HEADWORD: merchant marine
<hw>mer"chant ma*rine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The ships
owned by nationals of a particular country that are engaged in civilian
commerce; also, the personnel operating those vessels. Distinguished
from the <contr>navy</contr>, which contains the vessels of
war.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>merchantry</ent>⟦br⟧
